HEADWORD: Carolus
<hw>Car"o*lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Caroluses</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Caroli</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., Charles.]</ety> <def>An English gold coin
of the value of twenty or twenty-three shillings. It was first struck in
the reign of Charles I.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Told down the crowns and <qex>Caroluses</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Macawlay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

